```jsx
import { useState } from 'react';

const QUESTIONS = [
  {
    question: "What is the capital of...",
    answers: ["France", "Germany", "Spain", ...],
  },
  // Add more questions and answers in a similar format
];

function App() {
  const [currentQuestionIdx, setCurrentQuestionIdx] = useState(0);
  const [selectedAnswer, setSelectedAnswer] = useState(null);

  const handleNextQuestion = () => {
    setSelectedAnswer(null);
    setCurrentQuestionIdx((currentQuestionIdx + 1) % QUESTIONS.length);
  };

  const handleAnswerSubmit = () => {
    // Implement scoring and team logic here, e.g., updating team scores or changing teams
    handleNextQuestion();
  };

  return (
    <div className="App">
      <h1>Custom Google Feud</h1>
      <h2>{QUESTIONS[currentQuestionIdx].question}</h2>
      {QUESTIONS[currentQuestionIdx].answers.map((answer, idx) => (
        <button
          key={idx}
          onClick={() => setSelectedAnswer(answer)}
          style={{
            backgroundColor: selectedAnswer === answer ? "blue" : "white",
          }}
        >
          {answer}
        </button>
      ))}
      <button
        onClick={handleAnswerSubmit}
        disabled={!selectedAnswer}
        style={{
          marginTop: "1rem",
          backgroundColor: selectedAnswer ? "green" : "gray",
        }}
      >
        Submit Answer
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

This template contains a minimal layout for the game, displaying questions and answers. The code allows users to select an answer and navigate to the next question after submitting an answer. You'll need to implement the game rules, scoring, and team logic based on the game rules suggested above.

Remember to add a CSS file to style the app and customize the interface to fit your needs.

